[SN]TITLE[SN]
Marc Roberts: Barnsley captain injured for final two games of season

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Barnsley captain Marc Roberts will miss their final two games of the season with an ankle injury, head coach Paul Heckingbottom has confirmed to BBC Radio Sheffield.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The centre-back, 26, went off at half-time at Bristol City last weekend.
He will miss Saturday's visit of Burton Albion and the Tykes' trip to Newcastle on the final day of this term, 7 May.
Heckingbottom's side are 14th in the table, two points above 15th-placed Wolves and two below Cardiff, in 13th.
